\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces Real-emotion and shuffled-emotion deltas vs.\ text-only, with $95\%$ paired bootstrap CIs over test authors. Across all three families (frozen MiniLM probes, set-attention $P{=}50$, set-attention $P{=}200$), the real-emotion CI overlaps the shuffled-emotion CI and both straddle zero. The negative-control logic implies emotion does \emph  {not} add robust incremental signal beyond text.\relax }}{6}{figure.caption.9}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:emotion-delta}{{3}{6}{Real-emotion and shuffled-emotion deltas vs.\ text-only, with $95\%$ paired bootstrap CIs over test authors. Across all three families (frozen MiniLM probes, set-attention $P{=}50$, set-attention $P{=}200$), the real-emotion CI overlaps the shuffled-emotion CI and both straddle zero. The negative-control logic implies emotion does \emph {not} add robust incremental signal beyond text.\relax }{figure.caption.9}{}}
